added.title: A Turtle Named Mrytle
added.description: A trip to the seashore brings the Baby Looney Tunes into contact with a just-hatched turtle that Melissa, apart from the rest because of her bossy attitude, names Myrtle. Melissa just loves little Myrtle and wants to keep her from walking into the ocean so she may take Myrtyle home for herself.

added.title: Flu the Coop
added.description: Baby Bugs and Baby Daffy decide to team up and unlike the other Baby Looney Tunes, fake having received their annual flu shots at the local clinic. The joke's on them when they awaken on the day of Granny's big party unable to have fun because they both have the flu.

added.title: Oh Brother, Warehouse Art Thou?
added.description: Baby Sylvester is overcome with angst because Granny's broken old chair, his favorite napping place, must be replaced by a new, unfamiliar piece of furniture. The other Baby Looney Tunes work together to help turn Sylvester's trepidation into enjoyment during their mammoth furniture-shopping adventure.

added.title: Baby Brouhaha
added.description: Overhearing Granny on the phone say she's expecting a baby, Baby Bugs goes into overdrive, revving up the Baby Looney Tunes to prepare to care for an infant.

added.title: Backstage Bugs
added.description: Baby Bugs can't wait to see his favorite children's musical group, The Wormies, and he absolutely thrills to the notion of possibly meeting his personal hero, Willie Wormie, backstage after the show. But Bugs fails to heed Floyd's warning about staying with the group in the crowded arena and suffers consequences when he gets separated from Floyd.

added.title: Bend it Like Petunia
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes learn all about soccer from Floyd, who surprisingly is an enthused soccer expert. At first awkward, Baby Petunia works the hardest and displays the best sportsmanlike attitude, eventually becoming the very finest all-around soccer player of all the Baby Looney Tunes.

added.title: Cock-A-Doodle-Doo-It!
added.description: On their first farm visit, the Baby Looney Tunes meet a young, dispirited rooster named Baby Foghorn Leghorn. They work together to build his self-confidence, unleashing powers of persuasion and elocution that even Foghorn never knew he had.

added.title: Blast Off Bugs
added.description: Baby Bugs tries to realize his dream of traveling to the moon while the Baby Looney Tunes are on a space museum visit.

added.title: A Mid-Autumn Night's Scream
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes first Halloween involves a costume contest for Lola, Melissa and Petunia, group trick-or-treating and Sylvester overcoming his fear of confronting an allegedly scary neighbor.

added.title: Save Our Cinnamon
added.description: Granny's sister's beloved bakery, Cakery Bakery Dock, home of her wonderful trademark cinnamon rolls, is being put out of business so her landlord can tear down the bakery to build a parking lot. This galvanizes the Baby Looney Tunes to work together to bake one giant cinnamon roll as a tourist attraction to save the bakery, a project that ends up involving the whole town.

added.title: Are We There Yet
added.description: During a long road trip, Floyd, obsessed with taking the Baby Looney Tunes to visit the distant, annual Acme Garlic Festival, endures countless variants of the universal kid question, are we there, yet? Despite Floyd's garlic agenda, fate has other plans.

added.title: Lights! Camera! Tweety!
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes are very eager to visit the local TV station, home of their favorite live children's show. When Floyd accidentally locks them inside the studio moments before airtime, they are forced to put on today's program all by themselves!

added.title: Duck's Reflucks
added.description: Baby Daffy has Baby Bugs right where he wants him, as the subject of his digital photography and at the mercy of his endless, egocentric creative whims.

added.title: Stop and Smell Up the Flowers
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes explore a world of botanic wonder as they search for just the right spot to plant a young lemon tree.

added.title: Firehouse Frolics
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes tour the local fire station, learning fire prevention tips from friendly Fireman Frank. Later, Baby Daffy, the most reluctant and uninterested participant, displays the most fire-fighting knowledge when he is suddenly tested by a real-life emergency at Granny's house.

added.title: Taz in Toyland
added.description: After Taz breaks all of his toys, Granny gives him one last chance to care for something.

added.title: A Secret Tweet
added.description: The babies plan a surprise birthday party for Tweety.

added.title: Comfort Level
added.description: Sylvester learns to live without his blankey.

added.title: Like a Duck to Water
added.description: Daffy overcomes his fear of the swimming pool.

added.title: School Daze
added.description: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing.

added.title: Things That Go Bugs in the Night
added.description: Bugs must find the courage to discover what's making scary noises outside.

added.title: The Creature from the Chocolate Chip
added.description: Sylvester eats all of Granny's cookies then makes up a cookie monster to blame.

added.title: Card Bored Box
added.description: Faced with nothing to do, the babies use a cardboard box and their imaginations to make playtime fun.

added.title: Time and Time Again
added.description: The babies learn the importance of telling time.

added.title: May the Best Taz Win
added.description: Lola learns she can't be the best at every sport.

added.title: Mine!
added.description: Daffy learns a lesson in doing the right thing when he finds a purse filled with money.

added.title: Sylvester the Pester
added.description: An attention-starved Sylvester won't let Granny have any time to herself.

added.title: Cat-Taz-Trophy
added.description: Sylvester and Taz team up to win a toy racecar derby.

added.title: Duck! Monster! Duck!
added.description: Daffy reads the babies a scary story, only to end up frightening himself.

added.title: The Brave Little Tweety
added.description: Tweety takes a role in a play too seriously and begins to believe he's a real superhero.

added.title: Puddle Olympics
added.description: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

added.title: A Lot Like Lola
added.description: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her.

added.title: Mother's Day Madness
added.description: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

added.title: Takers Keepers
added.description: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want.

added.title: To Tell the Tooth
added.description: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

added.title: Spin Out
added.description: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy.

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: The babies experience their first snowfall.

added.title: Shadow of a Doubt
added.description: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is.

added.title: Christmas in July
added.description: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

added.title: Bruce Bunny
added.description: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce.

added.title: Leader of the Pack
added.description: Daffy starts a secret password club for everyone except Bugs.

added.title: Flower Power
added.description: The babies all want to pick the best flowers for Granny but they end up destroying her garden.

added.title: Lightning Bugs Sylvester
added.description: Sylvester learns to overcome his fear of lightning.

added.title: Flush Hour
added.description: The babies learn the purpose of toilets.

added.title: I Strain
added.description: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

added.title: The Sandman Is Coming
added.description: Daffy thinks the Sandman is a monster that throws sand in children's eyes.

added.title: Some Assembly Required
added.description: Bugs gets a new toy with assembly required and has to learn to follow instructions.

added.title: All Washed Up
added.description: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath.

added.title: Did Not! Did Too!
added.description: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

added.title: Tea & Basketball
added.description: Sylvester wants to play tea with the girls while Lola wants to play basketball with the boys.

added.title: Who Said That?
added.description: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it.

added.title: Mr. McStuffles
added.description: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it.

added.title: Picture This!
added.description: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

added.title: Hair Cut-Ups
added.description: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut.

added.title: A Clean Sweep
added.description: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

added.title: Daffy Did It!
added.description: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying.

added.title: Pig Who Cried Woof
added.description: Petunia fakes emergencies. But when a real one arises, no one believes her.

added.title: The Magic of Spring
added.description: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

added.title: New Cat in Town
added.description: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving.

added.title: For Whom the Toll Calls
added.description: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill.

added.title: Cereal Boxing
added.description: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

added.title: Let Them Make Cake
added.description: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

added.title: Mind Your Manners
added.description: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny.

added.title: Petunia the Piggy Bank
added.description: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

added.title: A Pastime for Petunia
added.description: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests.

added.title: Pouting Match
added.description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

added.title: Wise Quacker
added.description: Melissa gets laughs doing hurtful impressions of the other kids, but she takes the jokes too far.

added.title: Yours, Mine...and Mine, Mine!
added.description: Daffy thinks if he shares his old toys, Granny will buy him all new toys.

added.title: Loose Change
added.description: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change.

added.title: Act Your Age
added.description: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

added.title: Who's Your Granny?
added.description: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities.

added.title: The Tattletale
added.description: Lola begins tattling on the other babies until her friends no longer want to play with her.

added.title: The Yolk's on You
added.description: Daffy and Melissa team up to play jokes on the other babies.

added.title: Baby-Gate
added.description: Melissa spreads rumors about the babies, and Bugs goes undercover to find the truth.

added.title: Never Say Try
added.description: Sylvester is a bad dancer and finger painter so he believes he'll never be good at anything.

added.title: Pair O' Dice Lost
added.description: Daffy feels defeated whenever things aren't going his way.

added.title: Melissa the Hero
added.description: Melissa brags about helping Petunia to the point of self-aggrandizement.

added.title: The Trouble with Larry
added.description: Petunia invents an imaginary friend to help her always get her way.

added.title: The Littlest Tweety
added.description: Tweety is tired of being overlooked because of his diminutive size.

added.title: In Bugs We Trust
added.description: Bugs uses the babies' money to buy different toys than he promised.

added.title: Cool for Cats
added.description: Sylvester believes a commercial that says eating Chewy Chomps will make him cool.

added.title: Time Out!
added.description: Bugs, Daffy and Taz are disciplined by having a time out in the corner.

added.title: Present Tense
added.description: The Baby Looney Tunes pitch in to make an Arbor Day gift for Granny while Baby Lola, who suggested they do so, tries to make Granny a present on her own.

added.title: The Neat and the Sloppy
added.description: A study in contrasts enlivens this odd couple's antics. Baby Daffy is the compulsive mess maker, and Baby Sylvester is the cleanliness freak.

added.title: Tell-A-Photo
added.description: As Granny assembles her photo album, the babies gather around to reminisce about all the happy times they've spent together.

added.title: Move It!
added.description: Overhearing Granny making a call to Manny the Mover, Baby Bugs and Baby Lola jump to the conclusion they're all moving away from Granny's house.

added.title: Unlock the Magic: The Beginning
added.description: The discovery of an ancient, lost gateway leads the Care Bears on a rescue mission in the Silver Lining, a realm of natural wonders and comical creatures in the clouds beyond the borders of Care-A-Lot. While there, new discoveries expand the mission, challenging Cheer, Grumpy, and the mission team to grow beyond their present abilities and help the denizens of the Silver Lining.

added.title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
added.description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

added.title: Nobody's Perfect
added.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

added.title: A Yoorg Awakening
added.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

added.title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
added.description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

added.title: The Big Whifflesnooze
added.description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

added.title: Mixed Signals
added.description: The team receives a video message from Tenderheart that their mission has successfully ended and they can return home. Cheer suspects something about the message is wrong, but other members of the team don't agree. Cheer courageously stands her ground and keeps the team together while she solves the mystery, and reveals the message was faked by Bluster.

added.title: Funshine's Un-fun Day
added.description: Funshine can't bring himself to tell Cheer he accidentally broke her beloved necklace. His attempts to repair the broken necklace end in failure, so he hides it. When Cheer wrongly thinks Dibble is responsible for the disappearance of the necklace, Funshine knows he must tell her the truth.

added.title: The Great Giggle
added.description: The Care Bears are to witness the annual blooming of the Pinata Tree, an ancient event that can only happen if the Keeper of the Tree sees something that makes him giggle. Good Luck's giggle-inducing entertainment act goes awry because he relies on his errant lucky shamrock for success. He must learn to forgo luck and practice his act instead.

added.title: Festival of Hearts
added.description: When two greedy gnomes steal Love-a-Lot's gift-making crystal heart, the Care Bears must get it back in time for the Festival of Hearts that they are holding for the Whiffles. In doing so, they have to teach the gnomes the meaning of caring.

added.title: An Almost Eggless Easter
added.description: When the Easter Bunny's beautifully-painted eggs are drained of their color, it looks like Dibble will miss her first Easter egg hunt - she's really been looking forward to it. The Bears must find a way to repaint all the eggs before the big day.

added.title: A Wish-Full Reunion
added.description: Mysterious flying hearts appear in Care-A-Lot and bring Wish Bear to the Silver Lining. She joins the Care Bears on a mission to bring a mystical mother bird's missing baby chicks home, and give a new home to an orphan bird.

added.title: The Birthday That Wasn't
added.description: Dibble misunderstands the Bears' intentions when they secretly make a plush toy Whiffle for her "Un-birthday." Thinking it's real and that the Bears love it more than they love her, she steals it and plans to leave it in the forest. She has second thoughts and returns her "rival" to her friends, only to learn that it's a gift to show their love for her.

added.title: The Big Rumble
added.description: A family of comically raucous rocks moves in near a Whiffle garden and drives them to distraction with their ground-pounding games. Funshine gets the rocks to leave. But when he learns their ground-pounding creates new soil, he must convince them to come back.

added.title: Three Cheers for Cheer
added.description: When hard-working Cheer exhausts her crew running a string of drills to protect a Whiffle orchard from possible emergencies, Share's belly badge accidentally creates two Cheer duplicates. Cheer takes a recreation break, unaware that her clones are working Share and the crew - who think they're the real Cheer - even harder.

added.title: The Badge of Courage
added.description: When Dibble dresses up as a superhero complete with a pretend belly badge, the Whiffles think she's the real thing and need her to confront an imaginary monster that they believe lives in a cave. She bravely enters the cave but loses her courage when she loses the belly badge, until Funshine convinces her that her bravery came from inside her.

added.title: One Wise Bear
added.description: The Bears become lost in the Valley of Whispering Winds, where voices whisper in their ears and make them lose faith in themselves. Racing to their rescue, Tenderheart leads them to the only one who knows the antidote to the words of the Winds: a mysterious old bear of great wisdom who teaches them a valuable lesson about listening to your heart.

added.title: Snow-verload
added.description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself, just as Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot! They're determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.

added.title: Hide and Sneak
added.description: Dibble is chosen as "It" in a Whiffle game of Hide-and-Seek. The game turns serious when Bluster traps the Bears inside the Cloudseeker. Dibble and Cheer must find the Whiffles and free her friends.

added.title: Share Your Care
added.description: Dibble plants the seeds of a strange bush outside of its natural environment, unaware that she has unleashed a disaster: The plant multiplies and begins to quickly spread. The Bears must find a way to stop its greedy growth before it crowds out all the other plants in the Silver Lining.

added.title: Return of the Gnomes
added.description: When Gus and Garth's greedy uncle makes his nephews forget the caring, sharing, and generosity they learned from the Care Bears and convinces them to return to their old selfish ways, the Bears must help them remember their caring hearts.

added.title: The Light in the Forest
added.description: Cheer bonds with a migrating firefly-like creature, called a Sparklewing, who stows aboard the Cloudseeker. The two become good friends, but there's a problem: Sparklewings must finish their migration to bring life-giving nutrients to the fields of the Silver Lining. Cheer's difficult and emotional parting with her new friend is only possible once they both accept that it's for a greater good.

added.title: Monsterplant
added.description: Bluster creates a mad scientist's monster from a clump of moss and sends it to scare the Whiffles away. The kindhearted Monsterplant just wants to be friends with them, but the Whiffles are frightened away by how he looks. Share and Dibble work together to show the Whiffles how nice Monsterplant is on the inside.

added.title: Neon Beach Party
added.description: Bluster and his Bad Crowd arrive at a lakeside beach for his summer vacation, unaware that the Care Bears are having their vacation on the opposite shore. Trapped inside Bluster's climate-control dome and forced to spend their vacations together, the Bears must find a way to make friends with their ill-tempered neighbors.

added.title: Power Outage
added.description: The Care Bears come to the aid of a group of Whiffles whose worries are blanketing their garden with such bad vibes that plants won't grow. When the Care Bear Stare isn't powerful enough to help, Grumpy comes to the rescue with the invention of a robotic Care Bear Stare amplifier.

added.title: Where Oh Where Has Our Funshine Gone?
added.description: When Funshine uses the Care Bears' work time to develop his latest comic book character, his creative playtime jeopardizes the success of the team's mission to a strange part of the Silver Lining.

added.title: Water, Water Everywhere
added.description: Grumpy doesn't believe Funshine's warning that an invisible "Big Blob in the sky" is stealing water from a Whiffle garden -- he has pulled too many practical jokes before. To save the garden and his own credibility, Funshine must discover the truth of the menacing "Big Blob."

added.title: The Ultimate Bad Seed
added.description: Malcom becomes the new boss of Blusterland when he tricks Bluster into letting him transfer his inner-badness into a Bad Seed, leaving Bluster a polite shell of his former self. To neutralize the dangerous Seed before Malcom can use it to turn the Silver Lining into a giant Blusterland, the Care Bears must transfer its bad energy back into the only thing that can hold it, Bluster himself!

added.title: Rise and Funshine
added.description: Funshine learns he can be as fearless as one of his super hero comic book characters when the Team falls into a magical sleep. To awaken them, he must transport them in the Cloudseeker to a special place in the Silver Lining - but he has never driven it before, and must learn from a comical "How To Pilot the Cloudseeker" video hosted by Grumpy.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: On a mission to a remote area of the Silver Lining, Cheer questions the directions from Bedtime's maps. Everyone else backs Bedtime: he's never been wrong before! When the directions turn out to be wrong and lead them into danger, Cheer must trust her instincts to find a way out of the mess.

added.title: Dibble's Dust-Up
added.description: Grumpy's determination to get the Cloudseeker clean is comically thwarted when Dibble befriends a stowaway trio of cute dust bunnies.

added.title: Finders Keepers
added.description: When Dibble loses her beloved playball, the Care Bears are shocked to discover it has been taken by the Keeper, a mysterious figure who collects and stores away all items lost in the Silver Lining. To regain possession of the ball, the Bears and Dibble must help the Keeper recover a loss of his own.

added.title: The Incredible Shrinking Bears
added.description: Frustrated that she's too small to reach even the bottom-most berries on a tree, Dibble becomes the tallest member of the team when a strange cloud of magical fog shrinks the Care Bears to miniature size. To save them, she must race against time to get them to a reversal-fog that will return them to their normal size.

added.title: Plunk to the Rescue
added.description: When Plunk discovers that Cheer and the Bears are working with Robbie to foil Bluster's latest bad scheme, he's eager to help out, even if Robbie objects and Cheer thinks it's best that he sits this mission out.

added.title: Once Upon a Rainbow
added.description: When Grumpy mysteriously loses his blue color in a far-off area of the Silver Lining, the Bears track down the cause: a creature called the Painter has lost the key to the magical paintbox that creates all the color in the area. Grumpy must recover the key to restore his blueness.

added.title: After the Klatternack
added.description: The Care Bears try to capture the Klatternack, a comical creature whose non-stop nonsense is annoying the local Whiffles. The Bears are joined by the ultra-serious Tracker, who has long been after the Klatternack himself. But despite their combined efforts, the wily creature continues to elude them - until Share realizes there is more going on than meets the eye.

added.title: Let the Fun Shine
added.description: Expert skateboarder Funshine tries to duplicate the in-the-groove fun Dibble has when she rides her little cloud like a skateboard, but he discovers along the way that having fun isn't always about a better skateboard or riding a cloud, it can be about trying harder at something and finally succeeding.

added.title: Valley of the Shamrocks
added.description: When Grumpy replaces mission navigator Good Luck with a computerized navigational gadget, Good Luck feels useless -- until he saves the Valley of the Shamrocks and is proclaimed a hero by the Whiffles, who don't want him to leave. He is torn between staying with the Whiffles and remaining with the Bears.

added.title: Some Luck
added.description: While the Bears are transporting a Whiffle Wizard to a distant meadow, Good Luck seems to have a run of bad luck. His belief in his own bad fortune causes him to lose confidence, causing ever more "bad luck." It's only when he understands that we make our own luck that his "luck" changes.

added.title: Out of the Cheer Zone
added.description: Two mischievous Whiffle kids come to play with Dibble, forcing Cheer to put her important work on hold to manage them. When she finds her "managing kids" skills lacking and her important work in jeopardy, she uses her skills as a leader to get the kids working as a team to help her complete her work while having fun at the same time.

added.title: Sorry Not Sorry
added.description: While observing an ancient Whiffle ritual, Grumpy accidentally steps on a sentient plant. When his apology sends the plant and Whiffles into an upset, Share helps him learn how to genuinely apologize from his heart, and that a real apology is about how the other person feels, not about yourself.

added.title: The Last Laugh
added.description: Disappointed when his friends don't laugh at his jokes, Funshine encounters the Laffinpuff, a magical comedian who grants Funshine's wish to make everyone think he's funny. But Funshine realizes it's no fun being funny when people laugh at everything he says, whether he means it to be funny or not. To get the wish rescinded, he must face the Laffinpuff in a grueling ordeal of slapstick humor.

added.title: Say What?
added.description: When Share magically has her voice stolen from her in a field of flowers, she and the other Bears must learn to listen so they can find her voice and solve the problem between the flowers and their Whiffle gardeners.

added.title: The Big Freeze
added.description: The Bears investigate the mysterious transformation of a tropical valley into a winter wonderland of snow. To return it to its natural state, Funshine must follow Dibble's example and give up something he wanted for himself.

added.title: Return to Care-A-Lot
added.description: Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot, determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.
